10:15.032 --> 10:17.616
- Joe is kind of going
above and beyond.

10:17.659 --> 10:19.159
- It's gonna be cool.

10:19.202 --> 10:20.744
It should give it
a really neat pattern.

10:20.787 --> 10:22.495
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:22.539 --> 10:25.665
- [exhales]
- Erich is still having problems

10:25.709 --> 10:27.334
with putting a channel
into his metal.

10:27.377 --> 10:28.710
Now using a grinder.

10:28.754 --> 10:30.420
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:30.464 --> 10:32.464
<i> - I'm trying</i>
<i> to split this stock.</i>

10:32.507 --> 10:34.299
<i> I am...</i>
<i> [sighs]</i>

10:34.343 --> 10:37.510
Really, uh, getting frustrated
with myself.

10:37.554 --> 10:39.387
<i> I've run half of my time out</i>

10:39.431 --> 10:41.056
just trying
to open the stock up.

10:41.099 --> 10:44.267
I'm concerned greatly right now.

10:44.311 --> 10:46.978
<i> At this point I'm thinking,</i>
<i> "Holy [bleep].</i>

10:47.022 --> 10:49.522
<i> This is not looking good.</i>
<i> How am I gonna get this done?"</i>

10:49.566 --> 10:52.442
And quite frankly, I'm starting
to feel sick to my stomach.

10:52.486 --> 10:54.903
Wish I could crawl into
that dunk tank.

10:54.946 --> 10:56.946
- Two hours has elapsed!

10:56.990 --> 11:00.867
You have only
60 minutes remaining!

11:00.911 --> 11:03.912
- I'll take another two hours.

11:03.955 --> 11:06.831
- Walter's got his billet set.

11:06.875 --> 11:08.583
He's been working
on getting his can off.

11:08.627 --> 11:11.628
He's having
a little bit of trouble.

11:11.672 --> 11:14.422
<i> - For the canister,</i>
<i> I'm using a hammer.</i>

