21:03.471 --> 21:04.971
<i> but first I got</i>
<i> to fix the mistake,</i>

21:05.014 --> 21:06.931
and that's the bend in my blade.

21:06.975 --> 21:10.309
- Would you say that Joe has the
most work to do in this round?

21:10.353 --> 21:11.852
- He's got an extra step
in there, definitely.

21:11.896 --> 21:13.521
- Okay.

21:13.564 --> 21:15.106
<i> - I'm making</i>
<i> a straightening jig</i>

21:15.149 --> 21:17.149
designed to push that blade

21:17.193 --> 21:19.193
and straighten everything
in line.

21:19.237 --> 21:22.613
- Smart move.
- Joe's a survival instructor.

21:22.657 --> 21:24.156
- Yeah, and survival is about

21:24.200 --> 21:27.243
how to be able
to adapt to situations,

21:27.287 --> 21:29.287
and Joe's showing a lot
of those skills.

21:29.330 --> 21:32.123
<i> - I have to get this thing</i>
<i> straight as possible.</i>

21:32.166 --> 21:34.166
If I'm not careful,

21:34.210 --> 21:36.294
I could destroy my blade.

21:36.337 --> 21:39.213
<i> [rock music]</i>

21:39.257 --> 21:41.882
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:41.926 --> 21:45.303
- My game plan is to get
the geometry fixed

21:45.346 --> 21:47.096
and start the handle.

21:47.140 --> 21:50.850
To me, the heart of this blade
is the blade itself.

21:50.893 --> 21:54.395
If the geometry's not correct,
if the edge is not sharp

21:54.439 --> 21:56.605
<i> then it's gonna fail</i>
<i> in the test.</i>

21:56.649 --> 21:59.400
I get nervous
when I think about failing.

21:59.444 --> 22:02.611
- I'm hoping he's not removing
too much material from that,

22:02.655 --> 22:04.238
lightening it up too much.

22:04.282 --> 22:06.699
- Yeah, 'cause I'm gonna cut
a bone with it.

22:06.743 --> 22:08.993
- Let me just on my soapbox.

22:09.037 --> 22:10.870
The very first thing
I'm gonna have to do

22:10.913 --> 22:13.039
is grind off those barnacles.

22:13.082 --> 22:15.041
- I don't know how he managed
to make that thing

22:15.084 --> 22:17.543
appear to be 3,000 years old.

22:17.587 --> 22:19.086
- That's what I get paid for.

22:19.130 --> 22:21.547
I think he's doing a good job.
[laughs]

22:21.591 --> 22:23.924
- Edge geometry on this is
a little rough right now,

